19 Sec. B-1. 5 MRSA §81, as amended by PL 1977, c. 674, §1, is further amended to
20 read:
21 §81. Office and duties; vacancy; salary; expenses; fees
22 The Department of the Secretary of State, as heretofore established, shall consist
23 consists of the Secretary of State, the State Archives and such other state departments and
24 agencies as are by law subject to the direction of the Secretary of State. The secretary shall
25 keep his the Secretary of State's office at the seat of government; have the custody of the
26 state seal and preserve all records in such that office, at the expense of the State. The
27 Secretary of State may appoint deputy secretaries of state who shall serve at the pleasure
28 of the Secretary of State. The secretary shall designate one of his the deputies as first deputy
29 secretary of state. When a vacancy happens in the office of Secretary of State during the
30 recess of the Legislature, the first deputy secretary of state shall act as Secretary of State
31 until a Secretary of State is elected by the Legislature. Such That deputy shall take the oath
32 required of the elected Secretary of State and must have the same compensation while he
33 performs performing the duties of the office.
