15 Sec. B-3. 8 MRSA §271, sub-§2, as amended by PL 2019, c. 626, §§4 to 6, is
16 further amended to read:
17 2. Minimum number of race days; criteria for date awards. The commission shall
18 determine the number of race days that should be awarded to licensed applicants pursuant
19 to this section based on the criteria set forth herein. The commission may award fewer than
20 the minimum race days set forth in section 275‑A, subsection 1 to commercial tracks with
21 the express written approval of the track, and with the express written approval of an
22 association of horsemen horse owners, trainers and drivers as defined in section 272‑B, if
23 credible evidence is presented that demonstrates that fewer race days is in the best interest
24 of Maine's harness racing industry. The award of fewer race days than set forth in section
25 275‑A, subsection 1 may not affect the status of those tracks as commercial tracks pursuant
26 to section 299. In assigning race dates to licensees, the commission shall consider the
27 following factors:
28 A. The revenues to be generated, consistent with the profitability and financial health
29 of the licensee and the development of revenues from interstate simulcasting of the
30 licensee's race programming, for the operating account pursuant to section 287; the
31 purse supplements pursuant to section 286; the Sire Stakes Fund pursuant to section
32 281; and the Stipend Fund pursuant to Title 7, section 86;
33 B. The quality of race programming and facilities offered and to be offered by the
34 licensee, the suitability of the applicant's racing facilities for operation at the season for
35 which the race dates are requested and the ability of the applicant to offer racing at
36 night;
37 C. The necessity of having and maintaining proper physical facilities for racing
38 meetings, including the ability to maintain ownership of or a leasehold on the facilities;
39 and consequently, to ensure the continuance of the facilities, the quality of the
40 licensee's maintenance of its track and plant, the adequacy of its provisions for
41 rehabilitation and capital improvements and the necessity of fair treatment of the
42 economic interests and investments of those who, in good faith, have provided and
43 maintained racing facilities;
