16 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
17 number to read consecutively.
18 SUMMARY
1199 This amendment removes from Part A, sections 10, 37 to 48, 59 to 62, 69, 80 and 81.
2200 The amendment amends Part A, section 23 by adding clarifying language describing orders
2211 of attachment. It adds a section correcting outdated, gender-specific language and outdated
2222 terminology in the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 5, section 81. It corrects outdated, gender-
2233 specific language in Title 8, sections 262 to 1037. It adds a section removing language
2244 describing married women in Title 10, section 3251.
